15/06/2009
TIRANA, Albania -- The deadline for Albanians to apply for new electronic ID cards expires on Monday (June 15th). Under the country's new election code adopted last December, only citizens holding a valid passport or electronic ID card will be allowed to cast their vote in the parliamentary elections on June 28th. The interior ministry said in a statement a total of 1,354,000 citizens have so far applied, while 1,253,000 cards have been produced. 
In other news, police arrested a suspected human trafficker on Sunday, detaining him on the road between Gjirokastra and the Greek border. Police officers found eight other Albanians travelling separately in two cars. They admitted paying 2,000 euros each to make an illegal crossing into Greece. (Gazeta Shqiptare, Shqip, Balkan Web, Shekulli - 15/06/09; Shekulli, Top Channel, Ora News, Balkan Web - 14/06/09) 
